at covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log (the log covers the full day, not just this session)\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report\n4. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n5. **What went wrong** — the status update gap that caused this session to be needed\n6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n7. **Action items** — concrete next steps\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md. Since a retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":468,"cache_read_input_tokens":62675,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":468},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a908014f-d8c1-4190-a7af-fc4ed83f4f35","uuid":"ac691539-0dff-4ecd-a84b-c48cf6ad5214"}
