{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SQnLYWF1X1D5BWE8DuzCJV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JKwZAp8c8zYqdKHRftSVaP","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat >> /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md << 'RETRO_EOF'\n\n---\n\n# Session 32 Retrospective — 2026-03-28T16:30\n\n## Session Summary\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Session number | 32 (Ralph loop iteration 11) |\n| Stories attempted | 2 (16-7, 16-8) |\n| Stories completed | 2 (both marked done) |\n| Epic 16 status | COMPLETE (8/8 stories) |\n| Sprint status | ALL_DONE (74/74 stories, 17/17 epics) |\n| Productive new code | None — this was a status-update-only session |\n\n**What happened:** Stories 16-7 and 16-8 had already been fully implemented, reviewed, and verified (ALL_PASS) in session 31. However, session 31 ended before the sprint-state.json status update from `review` to `done` was committed. This session re-verified both proofs, confirmed all tests pass (321/321, 96.85% coverage), updated their status to `done`, marked epic 16 complete, and committed.\n\n## Issues Analysis\n\nThe session issues log covers the full day (sessions 30-32). Categorized below:\n\n### Bugs Found and Fixed (7 total across day)\n\n| Severity | Count | Examples |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| HIGH | 1 | AC2 test false-pass risk in story 16-6 (fixed with Given/When/Then format validation) |\n| MEDIUM | 9 | indexOf guard, DRY violation, fragile section coupling (16-5); missing escalate tier test, weak AC8 assertions, silent empty-string fallback x2 (16-7) |\n| LOW | 5 | Section ordering mismatch, string-matching test brittleness (16-5); legacy term references, test count doc drift (16-6, 16-7, 16-8) |\n\nAll HIGH and MEDIUM bugs were fixed in-session. LOW bugs were documented but left as out-of-scope.\n\n### Recurring Issues\n\n1. **Ralph state corruption** — Still the dominant issue. Ralph's in-memory state overwrites sprint-state.json on each loop iteration, reverting stories 16-5 through 16-8 from `done` back to `review`. This has occurred in every session since session 17.\n2. **Pre-existing BATS failures** — 5 failures in `all_tasks_complete` suite noted during 16-6 verification. Unrelated to story work.\n3. **Legacy terminology** — `black.box` references persist in `patches/AGENTS.md`, `patches/retro/enforcement.md`, `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`. Out of story scope.\n\n### Subagent Token Report Aggregate\n\nAcross all subagent phases logged today (8 phases: 4 code-reviews + 4 verifications):\n\n| Phase | Tool Calls | Top Tools | Notable |\n|-------|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| 16-5 code-review | 27 | Read:10, Grep:8, Bash:6 | harness-run.md read 5 times |\n| 16-5 verification | 15 | Bash:10, Read:5 | npm test run twice |\n| 16-6 code-review | 19 | Bash:8, Read:7, Grep:3 | story test file run 3 times |\n| 16-6 verification | 15 | ~8 files read | minimal redundancy |\n| 16-7 code-review | 22 | Read:9, Grep:8, Bash:7 | redundant story file read, duplicate grep |\n| 16-7 verification | 16 | Grep:10, Bash:7, Read:2 | npm test run twice |\n| 16-8 code-review | 18 | Read:11, Glob:4, Bash:3 | no redundancy |\n| 16-8 verification | 14 | Bash:7, Read:6, Edit:3 | npm test run twice |\n| **TOTAL** | **146** | | |\n\n**Redundancy patterns identified:**\n- `npm test` run twice in 3 of 4 verification phases (once full, once grep-filtered). Could capture output once.\n- `harness-run.md` read 5 times by a single code-review subagent (different offsets, but could batch).\n- Story test files re-run 3 times in 16-6 code-review.\n- Two grep passes for `black.box` in 16-7 could have been combined.\n\n## Cost Analysis\n\n### Cumulative Sprint Cost (all sessions)\n\n| Metric | Previous (Session 31) | Current (Session 32) | Delta |\n|--------|----------------------|---------------------|-------|\n| Total API-equivalent cost | $716.85 | $872.21 | +$155.36 |\n| Total API calls | 5,268 | 6,354 | +1,086 |\n| Avg cost per story | $3.54 | $4.10 | +$0.56 |\n\nThe $155.36 increase covers sessions 31 and 32 combined (the stats tool does not separate by session). This includes the actual implementation/review/verification of stories 16-7 and 16-8 (session 31) plus the re-verification and status fix (session 32).\n\n### Cost Distribution\n\n| Category | Cost | % of Total |\n|----------|------|-----------|\n| Cache reads | $509.38 | 58% |\n| Cache writes | $226.78 | 26% |\n| Output tokens | $135.82 | 16% |\n| Input tokens | $0.22 | <1% |\n\n### Phase Cost (cumulative)\n\n| Phase | Cost | % | Observation |\n|-------|------|---|-------------|\n| verify | $466.24 | 53.5% | Dominant cost — verification is the most expensive phase |\n| orchestrator | $192.87 | 22.1% | Ralph loop overhead |\n| retro | $102.84 | 11.8% | 35+ no-op sessions generating retros adds up |\n| code-review | $43.15 | 4.9% | Reasonable for the rigor applied |\n| create-story | $37.05 | 4.2% | Story creation |\n| dev-story | $30.07 | 3.4% | Actual implementation is the cheapest phase |\n\n### Cost Waste Estimate\n\n| Source | Estimated Waste |\n|--------|----------------|\n| Ralph state corruption (35+ no-op sessions) | $150-250 |\n| \"unknown\" cost bucket | $224.38 (25.7% of total — still unattributed) |\n| Redundant npm test runs in subagents | ~$5-10 |\n| Re-verification in session 32 | ~$10-20 |\n\n## What Went Well\n\n1. **Sprint complete.** All 74 stories across 17 epics are done. 321 tests passing, 96.85% coverage.\n2. **Code review quality.** The multi-phase review process (code-review -> verification) caught 1 HIGH and 9 MEDIUM bugs before merge. No stories were sent back for re-development.\n3. **Verification rigor.** All stories achieved ALL_PASS on their acceptance criteria. No partial passes accepted.\n4. **Epic 16 delivery.** The verification tier system (8 stories) shipped cleanly — classification, parsing, proof validation, harness dispatch, story criteria, knowledge docs, and tests all updated.\n5. **Test infrastructure.** Coverage stayed above 96% throughout, with the 80% per-file floor enforced across all 158 source files.\n\n## What Went Wrong\n\n1. **Status update gap.** Session 31 completed all work for stories 16-7 and 16-8 (implementation, review, verification) but ended before committing the `done` status update. This forced session 32 to exist solely to re-verify and update status. Estimated waste: $10-20.\n2. **Ralph state corruption persists.** 35+ sessions have been wasted on the same bug. Ralph's in-memory state snapshot predates epic 16 completion and overwrites the file on every iteration. The `registerStory` guard from session 22 only prevents phantom stories, not status reversion.\n3. **No sprint-complete exit condition.** Ralph continues looping even when all 74 stories are done. Each loop costs orchestrator + retro overhead ($5-10 per iteration).\n4. **$224 in unattributed costs.** The \"unknown\" bucket in the cost report (25.7% of total spend) remains unattributed across all retros.\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\n### Patterns to Repeat\n- **Adversarial code review before verification** catches real bugs (HIGH/MEDIUM) early. Worth the cost.\n- **Structured session issues log with token reports** from each subagent enables retrospective cost analysis at the subagent level.\n- **Per-file coverage floor (80%)** prevents coverage gaming where a few well-tested files mask untested ones.\n\n### Patterns to Avoid\n- **Status updates must be atomic with verification.** When a story passes verification, its status should be updated and committed in the same operation, not deferred.\n- **Holding state in memory across loop iterations** without a freshness check is the root cause of the corruption bug. State should be read-modify-write with version checking.\n- **Running `npm test` twice in verification** (once for full output, once grep-filtered) wastes tokens. Capture once, filter from capture.\n\n## Action Items\n\n| Priority | Action | Status |\n|----------|--------|--------|\n| **P0** | Sprint is complete. Plan next sprint or close out. | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P0** | Fix Ralph state corruption — add compare-and-swap or monotonic version to state writes | CRITICAL — 35+ occurrences, $150-250 estimated waste |\n| **P0** | Add sprint-complete exit condition to Ralph's main loop | CRITICAL — stops wasting sessions |\n| **P1** | Make verification -> done status transition atomic with commit | Reinforced by session 32 gap |\n| **P1** | Attribute the \"unknown\" cost bucket ($224.38, 25.7%) | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Add subagent guideline: capture test output once, grep from capture | CARRY FORWARD — 3/4 verifications ran npm test twice |\n| **P2** | Tier verification depth by story complexity | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P2** | Add bash version check or shellcheck enforcement for ralph scripts | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up legacy terms (black.box references) in patches/templates | CARRY FORWARD |\n| **P3** | Clean up `1-1-foo` phantom story references from tracking data | CARRY FORWARD |\nRETRO_EOF","description":"Append session 32 retrospective to existing retro file"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":434,"cache_read_input_tokens":25211,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":434,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YU1sXbegSqZAToq2zSsPas","session_id":"a908014f-d8c1-4190-a7af-fc4ed83f4f35","uuid":"addaaafa-2e33-4f8c-8b95-3c1d2fb01a67"}
